issue.title: Collect more keywords by default
Response including empty trends
issue.body:
```js
{
    "name": "#IStillNeedAnEmojiFor",
    "rank": 9,
    "sentiment_score": null,
    "sentiment_description": null,
    "tweets_analyzed": 0,
    "articles": [],
    "tweets": [],
    "keywords": [],
    "locations": ["US"],
    "tracking_since": 1496131963
}
```

Do we want to include trends whose data has not been analyzed as part of the API response?

issue.title: Add more descriptive error messages
issue.body: We should return text that says something like "Invalid endpoint" with a 404 rather than "Cannot Get /", which is returned by default by Express.

issue.title: Remove rank attribute from alltrends endpoint
issue.body: Rank attribute shouldn't be there as the returned array is already sorted by rank.

issue.title: Collect more keywords by default
Track trends on startup even if next interval is not immediate.
issue.body:
If the time to the next server interval is > 0 because the backend has been restarted, we don't start tracking trends via the streaming API until the next update.

https://github.com/SentiSocial/backend/blob/master/app.js#L41

issue.title: Log the value of NODE_ENV on startup
issue.body:
Should be set to 'production' when running in production. We should log it on startup to make it clear what environment it's running in.

https://expressjs.com/en/advanced/best-practice-performance.html

issue.title: Use the async version of storage.getItem
issue.body:
https://github.com/SentiSocial/backend/blob/master/app.js#L56

This is run once every server interval, synchronous functions like this should only be run at initial startup. We should be using the async version instead.

issue.title: Add a way to get the the amount of time to the next server update
issue.body: This would be useful for debugging and also be an interesting piece of information to display on the frontend.
